# The `InductiveRangeCheck` Class Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

An inductive range check is conditional branch in a loop with a condition that is provably true for some contiguous range of values taken by the containing loop&#39;s induction variable. <a href="#details">More...</a>

## Description {#details}

An inductive range check is conditional branch in a loop with a condition that is provably true for some contiguous range of values taken by the containing loop&#39;s induction variable.

Definition at line 137 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/transforms/lib/transforms/scalar/inductiverangecheckelimination-cpp">InductiveRangeCheckElimination.cpp</a>.

## Public Member Functions

### computeSafeIterationSpace() {#a5591acf152c652226d89a2b5ea436d05}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>std::optional&lt; InductiveRangeCheck::Range &gt; InductiveRangeCheck::computeSafeIterationSpace (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scalarevolution">ScalarEvolution</a> &amp; SE, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scevaddrecexpr">SCEVAddRecExpr</a> &#42; IndVar, bool IsLatchSigned) const</>}>
Computes a range for the induction variable (IndVar) in which the range check is redundant and can be constant-folded away.

Computes and returns a range of values for the induction variable (IndVar) in which the range check can be safely elided.

The induction variable is not required to be the canonical &#123;0,+,1&#125; induction variable.

If it cannot compute such a range, returns std::nullopt.

### parseRangeCheckICmp() {#af080850b5b14a209bf3fa2aef6da2725}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool InductiveRangeCheck::parseRangeCheckICmp (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/loop">Loop</a> &#42; L, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/icmpinst">ICmpInst</a> &#42; ICI, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scalarevolution">ScalarEvolution</a> &amp; SE, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scevaddrecexpr">SCEVAddRecExpr</a> &#42;&amp; Index, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scev">SCEV</a> &#42;&amp; End)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Parse a single ICmp instruction, <code>ICI</code>, into a range check.

If <code>ICI</code> cannot be interpreted as a range check, return false. Otherwise set <code>Index</code> to the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scev">SCEV</a> being range checked, and set <code>End</code> to the upper or lower limit <code>Index</code> is being range checked.
